<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Eof on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/eof/</link><description>Recent content in Eof on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/eof/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Go EOF Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="eof--end-of-file-fix"&gt;EOF — End of File Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An EOF (End of File) error occurs when a read operation reaches the end of the data source. In Go, &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is returned by &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; to indicate no more data is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is not a true error — it&amp;rsquo;s a signal that the read operation completed successfully but there&amp;rsquo;s no more data. Many Go APIs return &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; on the final &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; call. Failing to handle &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; properly causes programs to treat a normal end-of-data condition as an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go EOF Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="eof--end-of-file-fix"&gt;EOF — End of File Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An EOF (End of File) error occurs when a read operation reaches the end of the data source. In Go, &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is returned by &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; to indicate no more data is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is not a true error — it&amp;rsquo;s a signal that the read operation completed successfully but there&amp;rsquo;s no more data. Many Go APIs return &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; on the final &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; call. Failing to handle &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; properly causes programs to treat a normal end-of-data condition as an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java MarshalException — Marshalling EOF Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/marshallingeofexception/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/marshallingeofexception/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="marshalexception--marshalling-eof-fix"&gt;MarshalException — Marshalling EOF Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;MarshalException&lt;/code&gt; (also referred to as &lt;code&gt;MarshallingEofException&lt;/code&gt;) is thrown when an error is detected during the marshalling or unmarshalling of data. This commonly occurs when reading past the end of a stream (EOF) while deserializing or parsing structured data. It is a subclass of &lt;code&gt;IOException&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The exception occurs when the marshalling framework encounters unexpected end-of-stream while trying to read structured data. This typically means the data source is truncated or corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Broken Pipe — Pipe Closed Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/broken-pipe-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/broken-pipe-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="broken-pipe--pipe-closed-error"&gt;Broken Pipe — Pipe Closed Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An IO error with the message &amp;ldquo;Broken pipe (os error 32)&amp;rdquo; occurs when you write to a pipe or socket whose reading end has been closed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Unix, pipes connect processes — stdout of one to stdin of another. When the reader exits, the writer gets a &lt;code&gt;SIGPIPE&lt;/code&gt; signal. Rust ignores &lt;code&gt;SIGPIPE&lt;/code&gt; by default and returns an IO error instead (error code 32, &lt;code&gt;EPIPE&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>End of file</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cobol/end-of-file/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cobol/end-of-file/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An end of file (EOF) condition occurs when a READ statement attempts to read past the last record in a sequential file. This is indicated by FILE-STATUS 10 and the AT END clause.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reading past last record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing AT END handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empty file&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect loop termination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cobol" data-lang="cobol"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PROCEDURE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DIVISION&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; MAIN-PROCEDURE.&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;OPEN&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INPUT&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PERFORM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;UNTIL&lt;/span&gt; WS-FILE-STATUS &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;10&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;MOVE &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;10&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TO&lt;/span&gt; WS-FILE-STATUS&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;NOT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DISPLAY&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-RECORD&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END-READ
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END-PERFORM
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CLOSE&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cobol" data-lang="cobol"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PROCEDURE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DIVISION&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; * Alternative: Use AT END flag
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;OPEN&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INPUT&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;MOVE &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;N&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TO&lt;/span&gt; WS-EOF-FLAG&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PERFORM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;UNTIL&lt;/span&gt; WS-EOF-FLAG &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Y&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;MOVE &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Y&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TO&lt;/span&gt; WS-EOF-FLAG&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;NOT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; PROCESS-RECORD&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END-READ
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END-PERFORM
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cobol" data-lang="cobol"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; * Example 1: Missing AT END
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; * May get FILE-STATUS 10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; * Example 2: Empty file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;OPEN&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INPUT&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DISPLAY &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;File is empty&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END-READ
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; Example &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;: Loop without EOF check&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PERFORM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;UNTIL&lt;/span&gt; FALSE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt; EMPLOYEE-FILE&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DISPLAY&lt;/span&gt; WS-RECORD&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt; * Infinite loop if no EOF handling
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cobol/file-status"&gt;File status error&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cobol/locked-record"&gt;Record locked&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby EOFError — End of File Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/eof-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/eof-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="eoferror--end-of-file-fix"&gt;EOFError — End of File Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;EOFError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when the end of a file or stream is reached during a read operation like &lt;code&gt;gets&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;readline&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;EOFError&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you try to read beyond the end of a stream. This is common with interactive input (&lt;code&gt;STDIN&lt;/code&gt;), network sockets, and sequential file reads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STDIN at EOF&lt;/strong&gt; — input redirected from file or pipe ends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Socket closed by peer&lt;/strong&gt; — remote end closed connection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reading past end of file&lt;/strong&gt; — multiple reads without checking EOF.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;gets on empty stream&lt;/strong&gt; — no data available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: STDIN at EOF (piped input)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;line1 &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; gets &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# &amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;line2 &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; gets &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# EOFError if only one line available&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Socket closed by remote end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPSocket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;gets &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# EOFError if connection closed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Reading after all data consumed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;File&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;open(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;gets &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# First line&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;gets &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Second line&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;gets &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# EOFError if file has only 2 lines&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-for-nil-return-from-gets"&gt;Fix 1: Check for nil return from gets&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — doesn&amp;#39;t handle EOF&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;line &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; gets
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;puts line&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# NoMethodError on nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — gets returns nil at EOF&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (line &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; gets)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts line&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;chomp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-readline-with-eof-rescue"&gt;Fix 2: Use readline with EOF rescue&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; line &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;STDIN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;readline
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EOFError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-ioforeach-for-file-iteration"&gt;Fix 3: Use IO.foreach for file iteration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — handles EOF automatically&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;File&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;foreach(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;line&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; process(line)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-handle-socket-eof"&gt;Fix 4: Handle socket EOF&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPSocket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (line &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;gets)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; process(line)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EOFError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Connection closed by remote end&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ensure&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;close
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="io-error"&gt;IOError&lt;/a&gt; — stream closed during operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="connection-refused"&gt;Errno::ECONNRESET&lt;/a&gt; — connection reset by peer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="io-wait-error"&gt;IO::WaitReadable&lt;/a&gt; — read would block (non-blocking I/O).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>